Here is one for ya.<br>
I was camping a 6hr named spawn with another, when someone logged on and said they were camping this spot and had logged out to let parent use the phone for 5 mins.<br>
I had been here for almost 30 min and understanding a parent or spouse situation we told him we were leaving and letting him/her have the spot. Then this person started getting really rude because we didn't leave right then, which I was talking to another friend to join them somewhere else, telling us we had to leave now and kept sending us all kinds of tells such as: his spot, he was camping it first, we were KS, he had been there all day, etc., then he started following my partner around checking his inventory about 20 times and wanting to get in a debate about camping issues.<br>
    We sent out a report and petition, in 10 mins a GM responded (really quick for a GM) The GM's response is &quot;There is no camping of any kind, whomever the mob agroes on first is whom it belongs to.&quot; So I asked does that include rare named spawns and his reply was yes, there is no camping and mob belongs to first agroe. The GM also came into the zone and was talking with the rude person as to what happened and said we could come back to that spot. I do not know what happened for I left to go somewhere else to help another friend. <br>
     My thought is, if it is a rare spawn I won't take there camp, otherwise normal mobs I will share.<br>
     <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 511<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/12/02 8:11:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2880.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: afk at a 'camp'...?</span><hr size=1> 10 minutes sounds good for most.  Of course, if it's a rare spawn that despawns, then things change.<br>
<br>
I remember way back camping the Testament of Venear guy.  I'd probably spent 30 hours there in different camps; 2-3 hours at a time.  Well, I popped in again, and there was someone standing nearby.  Not afk when I sent him a tell (pre-AFK tag), and no response.  I decided to work on some spell mastery as I'd just leveled up, so started casting.  Every couple a minutes I sent a new tell.  Nothing.  After 20 minutes, Dyllan pops.  I sent one more tell after a minute, and when nothing happened, I blasted him.<br>
<br>
